<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: BENDIX - TROUBLESHOOTING - 2000, 4000 &#38; 8000 MODELS - TROUBLESHOOTING
        - TESTING FOR FALSE INDICATION CAUSED BY ABS WARNING LIGHT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TESTING FOR FALSE INDICATION CAUSED BY ABS WARNING LIGHT</title>
        <para>This test should be performed if: 1. The ABS Warning Light on the instrument panel remains ON, 2. There
            are no Red LEDs ON, 3. The Green VLT LED Is ON but not flashing.
        </para>
        <table id="t0403317" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing For False Indication Caused by ABS Warning Light</title>
            <tgroup cols="6" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.73in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.74in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.69in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="1to6"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>STEP</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>KEY</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>ACTION</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>YES / IN SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6">
                            <para>NO / OUT OF SPEC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Hold magnet on LED reset and note if all LEDs illuminate.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>All LEDs ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (288) from controller. With key ON note if ABS Warning Light is
                                ON.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>ABS light ON.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace the controller.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Do not reconnect (288) at this time. Remove ABS Warning Light relay from connector
                                (284). Measure resistance to ground at circuit 94H.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 94H between connectors (284) and (288), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove ABS Warning Light Bulb from cluster, then at connector (284) measure resistance
                                to ground at circuit 94E.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace ABS Warning Light Relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 94E between ABS warning light and connector (284),
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcproc>
